Comment: 0,0:03:46.86,0:03:46.86,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:226860,226860}Part A
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.02,0:03:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:227027,229129}Marie… please smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.12,0:03:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:229129,232699}Why, Marie?\NWhy don't you smile at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.50,0:03:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:233500,235535}Please, open your eyes, Marie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.86,0:03:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:235869,237337}Father…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.36,0:04:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:264364,266032}This is your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.03,0:04:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:266032,269803}You killed Marie.\NYou ruined the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.30,0:04:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:272305,276176}You killed Marie and\Ndestroyed the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.11,0:04:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:279112,280313}Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.31,0:04:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:280313,283717}Get out of my house.\NEveryone out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.71,0:04:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:283717,285919}It is my house.\NGet out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.45,0:04:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:286453,288188}Get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.18,0:04:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:288188,289389}Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.38,0:04:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:289389,293493}This is my house. None of you\Nare welcome here. Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.49,0:04:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:293493,294594}Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:04:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:296029,297764}What are you doing?\NWe have to run!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.19,0:04:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:298198,299833}Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.83,0:05:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:299833,302369}Get out of my house!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.70,0:05:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:302702,305806}Don't come near me. Out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.80,0:05:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:305806,308208}Leave, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.64,0:05:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:311645,314047}– Get out of here…\N– Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.38,0:05:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316383,316983}Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.98,0:05:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:316983,321054}Get out…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.40,0:05:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:336403,339139}Mr. Andréa,\NI can show you the way out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.13,0:05:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:339139,340540}What? Gaston?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.54,0:05:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:340540,344811}There is a secret passage\Nthat only I and my master knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.81,0:05:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:344811,345745}Follow me, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.98,0:05:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:346980,348114}Come on, Andréa.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.58,0:05:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:348582,349883}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.41,0:05:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:350417,352352}Everyone, follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.35,0:05:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:352352,353787}Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:354087,355689}Isabelle, you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.19,0:05:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:357190,358058}Isabelle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.29,0:06:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:358291,361061}No! I'm not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.06,0:06:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:361061,364931}I will not leave my father alone.\NI'm staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.46,0:06:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:365465,367734}Isabelle, come with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.36,0:06:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:368368,370704}I'll decide what to do myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.70,0:06:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:370704,374174}Andréa, if you want to defend Paris,\Nbe my guest. But I'm staying here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.17,0:06:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:374174,376576}I will not leave Mom and Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.97,0:06:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:376977,377978}Isabelle!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.97,0:06:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:377978,381181}Go now! Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.18,0:06:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:381181,384651}Andréa, you go first.\NI'll take care of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.65,0:06:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:384651,387454}You're not coming\Nwith us, Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.45,0:06:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:387454,391124}I'm sorry, Andréa, but as you know,\NI serve the Versailles government.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:391458,392592}Victor…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.15,0:06:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:393159,395195}I still want to believe\Nin the French army.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.96,0:06:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:395962,397097}I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.29,0:06:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:399299,401434}Talk some sense into Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.97,0:06:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:412979,415682}Everyone should\Nbe dead by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.55,0:07:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:420553,422989}Isabelle. Are you sure\Nthat you want to stay here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.55,0:07:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:424557,425792}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.59,0:07:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:427594,428862}I don't know…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.60,0:07:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:433600,436069}Why?\NWhy is this happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.06,0:07:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:436069,439105}Victor, explain it to me.\NWhat is this all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.91,0:07:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:443910,445378}Hands up, traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.87,0:07:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:445879,448181}Shut up! Do you have any idea\Nwho you're talking to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.31,0:07:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:449316,450717}Captain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.31,0:07:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:452319,456656}{\i1}Flames, raging like Léon's anger,\Ncompletely consumed the Rostains' estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.85,0:07:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:457857,461861}{\i1}The Rostain family fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.16,0:07:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:463163,464264}My master…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.26,0:07:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:464264,465432}My mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.65,0:08:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:484651,489322}{\i1}A few days later,\Nat the cemetery in Versailles
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.32,0:08:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:489322,493026}{\i1}a funeral was held\Nfor Léon and Marie Rostain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.69,0:08:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:493693,496997}{\i1}Since the Rostain family became\Ninfamous as traitors to the nation,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.99,0:08:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:496997,500867}{\i1}not many people\Ncame to the funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.55,0:08:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:518551,520720}Look, it's the daughter\Nof these subversives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.72,0:08:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:520720,524591}She's one cold piece of work.\NShe didn't even shed one tear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.59,0:08:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:524591,527227}What did you say?\NWould you like to say it again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.22,0:08:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:527227,531431}Ah, I just meant that\Nshe's very strong, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.63,0:08:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:531631,532766}You dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:08:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:534701,536036}Jean, leave him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.17,0:09:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:539172,542108}Please, don't make a scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.85,0:09:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:586853,589889}{\i1}The death of Marie and Léon,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.88,0:09:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:589889,592892}{\i1}and with it, the fall\Nof the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.25,0:09:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:593259,597464}{\i1}Isabelle still found it all\Nvery hard to believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.16,0:10:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:599165,603770}{\i1}However, the cold rain\Nkept pouring endlessly
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.77,0:10:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:603770,608708}{\i1}as if to remind Isabelle that\Nthe recent events really took place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.69,0:10:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:632699,634367}Isabelle…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.24,0:10:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:643243,646312}How was the Rostains' funeral?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.31,0:10:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:646312,648548}It must have been\Ngrandiose, no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.74,0:10:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:648748,650216}What is it that you\Nwant from me, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.88,0:10:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:650884,655455}This morning I received a secret letter\Nfrom Prussia. Here, read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.43,0:11:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:664430,665465}This… This is…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.10,0:11:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:667100,670303}Soon we will launch\Nan attack on Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.30,0:11:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:670303,673806}Within a short time we shall clean\Nthis city of the villains who occupy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.87,0:11:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:675875,679546}We will attack from this side,\Nand Prussia will strengthen us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.54,0:11:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:679546,683383}Because we will approach from the south,\Nthey will be like rats in a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.71,0:11:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:683716,688588}You want to join the enemy and launch a\Njoint attack on the capital? Are you for real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.58,0:11:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:688588,694460}That's right. The people who occupy Paris\Nraise their fists to their own government.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.46,0:11:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:694460,697864}They pose a threat to every country,\Nnot to mention Prussia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.86,0:11:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:697864,700867}As such, Prussia is more than\Nwilling to cooperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.86,0:11:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:700867,704103}Mr. Thiers, the people of Paris\Nare French, just like us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.47,0:11:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:704470,707774}You are wrong. The people\Nof Versailles are the real French.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.77,0:11:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:707774,709409}Not these knaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.40,0:11:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:709409,712745}Captain Langlois, you will\Ncommand the main attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.74,0:11:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:712745,716249}You want to make me\Nkill Paris citizens?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.24,0:11:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:716249,719285}The goal is to win back\Nthe capital and our properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.28,0:12:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:719285,723022}Anyone who objects shall not be spared,\Nnot even a woman or a child. Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.12,0:12:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:724123,725458}I have to refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.45,0:12:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:725458,726793}Excuse me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.06,0:12:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:727060,729128}I fight for France.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.12,0:12:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:729128,732131}I won't put my hand to killing\NFrench brothers and sisters!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.43,0:12:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:732432,734968}Disobedience means betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:735335,738705}I will not betray the people of France,\Neven if it means having to betray you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.77,0:12:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:739772,741574}So be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.57,0:12:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:741574,744077}Panza!\NArrest Captain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.07,0:12:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:744077,746613}For treason, I sentence him\Nto death by firing squad.
Comment: 0,0:12:32.68,0:12:32.68,Default,[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:752685,752685}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.05,0:12:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:754053,756956}Firing squad? For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.35,0:12:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:757357,762095}Versailles doesn't need you\Nanymore, Captain Langlois.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.09,0:12:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:762095,763429}Panza.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.50,0:12:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:769502,772739}Mr. Thiers, as a soldier\Nof the French army,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.73,0:12:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:772739,775441}I demand a legal trial\Nin front of the court martial.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.44,0:12:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:775441,778144}Captain Langlois, our attack\Non Paris will begin any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.14,0:13:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:778144,780913}I'm sorry, but we can't afford it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:780913,784250}In addition, I believe that\Nyou might know a bit too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.91,0:13:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:784917,786452}Thiers…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.45,0:13:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:786452,789289}Scoundrels like you\Nare the real enemy of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.65,0:13:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:789656,793793}I decide who is the enemy\Nof France and who is not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.79,0:13:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:793793,795161}Escort him out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.16,0:13:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:795161,796262}Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.26,0:13:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:796262,797997}Hands off!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.36,0:13:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:798364,800800}I can go alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.85,0:13:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:820853,822655}Isabelle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.65,0:13:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:822655,824424}Jean, I don't want to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.42,0:13:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:824424,828127}Oh, stop it. In such circumstances\Nit is best to talk as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.12,0:13:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:828127,830063}I want to see your smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.06,0:13:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:830063,833299}If it makes you laugh,\NI can even try to do a handstand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.29,0:13:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:833299,835935}Please, tell me.\NWhat can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.93,0:13:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:835935,837070}Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.07,0:14:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:837070,841641}So cold! Come on, there must be something.\NPlease tell me what it is. It can be anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.94,0:14:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:841941,844677}Jean, leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.67,0:14:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:844677,848915}I am the daughter of a traitor.\NMy house and property were confiscated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:848915,851951}You deserve more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.95,0:14:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:851951,854020}You'd better stay away from me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.02,0:14:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:854020,857323}Come on, now.\NWho I hang out with is my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.15,0:14:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:858157,860026}Why are you so stubborn?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.02,0:14:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:860026,862095}Please, leave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.69,0:14:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:862695,864097}Fat chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.09,0:14:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:864097,865932}What are you going to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.36,0:14:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:866366,867233}I'm going back to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.46,0:14:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:867467,868568}To Paris?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.73,0:14:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:869736,873039}Isabelle from Paris goes to defend Paris.\NI see that you regained your will to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.53,0:14:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:873539,875875}It's not quite like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.87,0:14:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:875875,879212}I just can't stand it here\Nat Versailles any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.21,0:14:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:879212,881681}Our mansion in Paris\Nis the only place I have—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.68,0:14:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:881681,884016}Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.31,0:14:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:884317,887353}Miss, terrible news!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.82,0:14:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:887820,888788}Jeanne?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.45,0:14:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:889455,892525}Mr. Victor has been\Narrested for treason!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.85,0:14:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:892859,893926}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.92,0:14:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:893926,897563}It's not all.\NHe's going to be shot tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.56,0:14:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:897563,898998}Shot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.27,0:15:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:907273,908941}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.51,0:15:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:913513,915848}What will I do without Victor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.84,0:15:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:915848,918518}No… I don't want\Nto think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.95,0:15:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:919952,922021}What to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.02,0:15:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:922021,924157}I'm sick of it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.26,0:15:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:932265,934600}Miss Isabelle,\Nplease remain calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.00,0:15:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:935001,937003}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.00,0:15:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:937003,940473}Isabelle, let's meet here\Ntoday at midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.47,0:15:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:940473,941874}Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.27,0:15:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:944277,946212}I'll give you a gift,\Nthe best you ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.95,0:15:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:953953,956589}I probably won't be\Ncoming back any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.06,0:16:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:967066,969669}Marie… Françoise…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.66,0:16:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:969669,971871}Brigitte… Sylvie…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.87,0:16:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:971871,976042}Yvette… Joanne… Delphine…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.04,0:16:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:976042,978945}Ha, I'm quite popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.94,0:16:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:978945,981347}But I didn't get even one\Nfrom Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.43,0:16:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:998431,999665}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.06,0:16:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1000066,1004537}We should be living at Versailles now,\Na life free of any worries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.53,0:16:46.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004537,1006839}What went wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.83,0:16:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1006839,1012345}But know that no matter what happens,\Nor how bad it will be, I will never leave you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.64,0:16:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1012645,1016516}Isabelle, I am going to save\Nthe man you love.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.51,0:16:58.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1016516,1018851}For you, I can do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1018851,1020186}Just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.55,0:17:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1020553,1022555}I always keep my word.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.00,0:17:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1040006,1041440}Young master?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.84,0:17:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1041841,1044310}My master called for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.31,0:17:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1044310,1045845}Gotcha. I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.94,0:17:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1049949,1051751}Did you call me, Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.75,0:17:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1051751,1053452}Ah, Jean. Would you like\Nto eat with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.45,0:17:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1053452,1056188}Unfortunately, I'm leaving soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.18,0:17:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1056188,1058925}Oh? Ah yes, you are\Nprobably going to a ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.92,0:17:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1058925,1060426}Uh… Yes, yes I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.42,0:17:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1060426,1062562}I understand. Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.56,0:17:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1062562,1066899}I'm just asking you not to hang out\Nwith that Isabelle of the Rostains.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.89,0:17:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1066899,1068200}Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.20,0:17:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1068200,1070770}Yes, Father.\NIt will be as you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.77,0:17:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1070770,1073606}Perfect. You can go now, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.60,0:17:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1073606,1075041}Yes, Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:17:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1076542,1078311}{\i1}Adieu and goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.69,0:18:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1095695,1097730}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.49,0:18:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1098497,1100566}Move away from the window\Nas far as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.13,0:18:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1101133,1103402}Jean? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.97,0:18:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1103970,1107173}We'll talk later. When I count\Nto ten, I'll blow up the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.54,0:18:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1107540,1109742}Ten. Nine. Eight. Seven. Six.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.74,0:18:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1109742,1112144}Five. Four. Three. Two. One!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.91,0:18:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1117917,1119118}Thank you, Jean.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.65,0:18:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1119652,1121921}I have prepared horses for us.\NFollow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.28,0:18:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1122288,1124056}– There!\N– They're running away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.05,0:18:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1124056,1126592}They're escaping!\NThey're climbing the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.85,0:18:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1126859,1129328}Three… Two… One!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.86,0:18:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133866,1135701}After them!\NDon't let them escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.63,0:19:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138638,1141774}Hell, so much more to climb!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.77,0:19:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1141774,1143976}Jean, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.67,0:19:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1144677,1145878}Don't let them escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.28,0:19:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1151283,1152184}Jean!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.15,0:19:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1153152,1155955}Damn! I will show you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.82,0:19:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1157823,1159959}They'll escape us!\NAfter them! Fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.95,0:19:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1159959,1160960}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.46,0:19:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1164463,1166432}Open the gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.26,0:19:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1169268,1170670}{\i1}Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.48,0:19:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1182481,1184684}Jean! Did you do all this\Nall by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.68,0:19:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1184684,1187386}Yes. I can do quite a lot\Nif I only apply myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.02,0:19:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1189021,1191190}Thank you.\NBut why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.19,0:19:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1191190,1193859}Isabelle needs you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.85,0:19:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1193859,1195227}Isabelle?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.22,0:19:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1195227,1197930}You must take her to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.93,0:19:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1197930,1199231}But, Jean…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.23,0:20:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1199231,1203169}Honestly, now that I saved you, I wouldn't\Nmind if you disappeared somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.16,0:20:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1203169,1206138}But Isabelle…\NShe loves you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.70,0:20:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1207707,1209742}Man, what a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.17,0:20:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1210176,1212611}Jean, but you\Nsurely know that…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.91,0:20:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1212912,1215448}Doesn't matter. For now, let's get\Nthe hell out of here as far as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.25,0:20:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1227259,1229729}Who would've thought that this kid\Nwould beat us to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.72,0:20:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1229729,1231864}Nice one, kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.33,0:20:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1235334,1237803}All right.\NWe'd better hurry as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.80,0:20:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1237803,1240372}The time has come.\NIt is time to fight for Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.37,0:20:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1240372,1242074}We will take our capital back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.07,0:20:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1242074,1243809}Yes sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.98,0:20:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1254987,1256088}Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.12,0:20:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1257123,1257790}Jean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.15,0:20:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1258157,1259825}Here's the gift I promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.72,0:21:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1261727,1262862}Victor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.86,0:21:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1262862,1264430}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.99,0:21:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1264997,1266565}Victor!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.73,0:21:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270736,1272938}Isabelle, I'm going to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.77,0:21:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1274774,1278878}I finally understood\Nwhat I should really protect.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.87,0:21:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278878,1281747}It is Paris.\NIt is the heart of France.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.91,0:21:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1282915,1284083}I'm going with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.38,0:21:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1284383,1286752}No. There will be\Nfighting everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.75,0:21:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1286752,1289855}It's too dangerous. I want you\Nto stay here and live happily.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.25,0:21:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1290256,1293159}No way. I will never\Nknow happiness here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.15,0:21:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1293159,1295528}Victor, please, take me with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.99,0:21:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1295995,1297863}I'm begging you, Victor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.43,0:21:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1298430,1301333}Take me… Take me\Nwith you to Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.33,0:21:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1301333,1302468}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.33,0:21:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1304336,1306172}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.60,0:21:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307606,1310009}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.88,0:21:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1314880,1316849}Hop on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.28,0:21:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1317283,1318150}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.21,0:22:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1319218,1321353}Please, take me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.35,0:22:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1321353,1325024}I don't have anywhere to go\Nwithout the Rostain family.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.02,0:22:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1325024,1326492}Jeanne?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.49,0:22:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1326492,1328427}You can come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.42,0:22:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1328427,1330462}Jean, are you coming\Nwith us, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.89,0:22:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1330896,1332765}I got used to the gunfire by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.76,0:22:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1332765,1336502}Versailles got too cramped\Nfor me as well, Isabelle.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.93,0:22:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1336936,1339605}Let's go!\NDirection – Paris!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.60,0:22:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1339605,1340739}Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.37,0:22:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1344376,1348347}{\i1}"Let's go to Paris."\N"Let's take our city back!"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.64,0:22:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1348647,1352184}{\i1}Andréa, Irma, Gaston…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.85,0:22:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1352852,1356021}{\i1}Isabelle, Victor, Jean…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.22,0:22:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1357223,1359258}{\i1}Finally, maid Jeanne.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.59,0:22:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1360593,1366432}{\i1}Over the clatter of horses' hooves, each of them\Nwas thinking about what would await them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.10,0:23:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1375107,1380446}{\i1}However, Paris was completely\Nsurrounded by Prussian army,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.44,0:23:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1380446,1387386}{\i1}and in Versailles, French troops commanded\Nby Thiers were already preparing to attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.62,0:23:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1388621,1393225}{\i1}The capital of France was stuck\Nbetween a rock and a hard place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.22,0:23:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1393225,1395461}Kill. Kill them all!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.46,0:23:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{TIME:1395461,1399064}Death to all who stand against us.\NParis is ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.49,0:23:56.36,Credits,[credits],0,0,0,,{TIME:1431497,1436368}{\fad(500,400)\c&HFAFAFA&\blur1\fs20\an5\pos(590,428)\t(2871,4871,4,\c&H101010&)}To be continued
